abstract: Chris and his husband quickly developed an app ten years ago to allow ordinary people to lobby the normally inaccessible and unelected House of Lords to pass the Same Sex Marriage Bill. It unexpectedly took off, helping the Bill overwhelmingly succeed in the normally-socially-conservative upper House of Parliament in the UK. Here's how they did it, and how coders can and should use their enviable skills to help change the world.
